commit.message:
Simplify history (#17)

A lot of stuff
f
pager fixup
Added pagination feature to webui. Currently some front end visualization needs to be done for prettiness.
f line endings
fix

Refactor: use Unix line endings, use double quotes

Create .gitattributes to enforce line endings to be LF.
Consistently use double quotes " instead of single quotes ' in strings.

Refactor: optimize CSS stylesheets

Use Sass SCSS to import Primer styles.
Use UnCSS to remove unnecessary styles.
Break up custom styles into multiple files for each page component.

Reduces the size of CSS from 140 KB for Primer alone (uncompressed) to
 - 9.3 KB for the "search" page bundle (uncompressed)
 - 8.2 KB for the "submission" page bundle (uncompressed)

This still leaves in some more unnecessary CSS, which we can remove
after some tweaking.

Feature: Labels on search page

Add "mixedcontent" and "default off" labels on the search page.
Refactor: Make Node exit on unhandled rejection

Feature: Implement functionallity of the /submit/ form

Web UI:
 - Add default_off form field.
 - Implement "Submit Pull Request" button handler.
 - Refactor: make search page links into anchors so that they can be opened
   in a new tab via context menu.
Server:
 - Create table schemas for ruleset updates proposals.
 - Implement server API endpoint that accepts form submissions.
 - Refactor: move database glue code from server.js to database/database.js.
 - Refactor: use SQL BOOLEAN instead of BIT(1).

Feature: Use Helmet to set security policies

Set "X-Frame-Options: DENY"
Set "Referrer-Policy: no-referrer"
Set Content Security Policy:
    default-src 'self'
    script-src 'self'
    style-src 'self'
    connect-src 'self'
    worker-src 'none'
    child-src 'none'
    base-uri 'none'
Set "X-Permitted-Cross-Domain-Policies: none"
Set default Helmet security headers
Refactor Web UI to remove inline JavaScript

Feature: Compress the network trafic

Use Express compression middlevare with default settings.

Refactor: Common style

Standard HTML and JS indentation (two spaces per indentation level).
Add docs/Style.md.
Remove dead code (code that is never run); this code can be brought back
later because it still is in git revision history.
Refactor a bit.

Refactor: add referential integrity constraints

Add foreign key constraints for all tables that use rulesets.rulesetid.
Add a few comments.

Publish documentation on GitHun Pages

Update documentation a bit.
Publish contents of /docs/ on GitHub Pages with theme
jekyll-theme-slate.

Simplify Web UI error handling

Let server do all query parameters checking.
This fixes a bug caused by server and Web UI checking for minimum
length of query but having different limits. Remove query length
check from Web UI altogether and instead let server do it and
respond with 400 "Bad request" and JSON {"message":[string]}
explaining the problem.

Revamp search page

In search results display rulesets with matching targets, not just targets.
This removes duplicate matches (if the same ruleset has multiple matching targets).
Remove possibility of SQL injection. Display actuall XML file on the ruleset details page.
Other minor improvements.

Don't chenge process current working directory

Pass the desired CWD as an argument to exec instead of changing the server-wide
directory. This ensures that is any other part of the server relies on CWD,
CWD won't suddenly change.

Initial prototype

This is a minimal working prototype, that supports:
 - Importing HTTPS Everywhere rules into database (Anton)
 - Importing Chromium HSTS preloa list into database (Anton)
 - Live updates of HTTPS Everywhere rules (Dylan)
 - Web UI: layout and scripts (Josh)
 - Web UI: networkin and database queries (Chris)
 - GitHub integration: create pull requests (Dylan)

This is the state of the project after the HackIllinois and a bit of refactoring.

Co-authored-by: Anton Bershanskiy <bershan2@illinois.edu>
Co-authored-by: Christopher Settles
Co-authored-by: Dylan Irlbeck
